{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778977743316,"sessionID":"ses_1ccaa862effe2snTZoyFM1CJi8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_0yq6dlLeyUSAaIScFJ71g2eg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"obo-grep.pl -r 'term_tracker_item:|gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:7711\"|gci_relation=\"part_of\"' src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo","timeout":120000,"workdir":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon","description":"Finds metadata and GCI style examples"},"output":"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /github/home/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e3356219e001WY4vWiioJ27S2Z\n\nn_notes \"The cannon bone of the 3-toed jerboa (jaculus jaculus) is the postnatal fusion of the 3 central metatarsals, which are distinct ossified elements prenatally\" xsd:string {source=\"PMID:22135653\", taxon=\"NCBITaxon:51337\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015241\nname: parapineal organ\nsynonym: \"parapineal gland\" RELATED []\nxref: TAO:0001360\nxref: ZFA:0001360\nis_a: UBERON:0003103 {source=\"ZFA\"} ! compound organ\nrelationship: in_lateral_side_of UBERON:0015238 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:117569\"} ! pineal complex\nrelationship: in_left_side_of UBERON:0015238 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:7954\"} ! pineal complex\nrelationship: never_in_taxon NCBITaxon:40674 ! Mammalia\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0015238 {source=\"ZFA\"} ! pineal complex\nproperty_value: external_definition \"An unpaired left-sided accessory organ which plays a role in establishing lateral brain left right asymmetry[ZFA:0001360, ZFIN:ZDB-PUB-030206-1].\" xsd:string {source=\"ZFA:0001360, ZFIN:ZDB-PUB-030206-1\"}\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"In lampreys and apparently in some fossil fish, the parapineal body and the pineal body (epiphysis) are a bilateral pair of structures rather than being located in series, one in front of the other. A pair of visual structures may have been the ancestral condition of this pineal complex (Weichert, 1970, p.622). The parapineal organs of lampreys, tadpoles, and lizards possess cells similar to rods and cones. Frogs possess a brow spot or frontal organ where ancestral pineal eye might have been (Weichert, 1970, p.622)\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0016879\nname: future central nervous system\nalt_id: UBERON:3000469\ndef: \"Primordium that develops into the central nervous system.\" [http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"future CNS\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"presumptive central nervous system\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: UBERON:0006598 ! presumptive structure\nintersection_of: has_potential_to_develop_into UBERON:0001017 ! central nervous system\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0000924 ! ectoderm\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0002346 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:7742\"} ! neurectoderm\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0016880 ! future nervous system\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018133\nname: monotreme bill\ndef: \"An elongated snout found in monotremes.\" [http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"beak\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"montreme beak\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"platypus beak\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"platypus bill\" NARROW []\nis_a: UBERON:0006333 ! snout\nrelationship: capable_of GO:0050964 {gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9257\", gci_relation=\"part_of\"} ! detection of electrical stimulus involved in electroception\nrelationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:9255 ! Monotremata\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018140\nname: mammary lobe\ndef: \"A cluster of mammary gland lobules. In humans this is a distinct lobe and located in the breast region.\" [http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"breast lobe\" NARROW HUMAN_PREFERRED [BTO:0004718, NCBITaxon:9606]\nsynonym: \"lobe of breast\" NARROW HUMAN_PREFERRED [BTO:0004718, NCBITaxon:9606]\nsynonym: \"lobe of mammary gland\" NARROW HUMAN_PREFERRED [BTO:0004718, NCBITaxon:9606]\nsynonym: \"lobi glandulae mammariae\" NARROW HUMAN_PREFERRED [BTO:0004718, NCBITaxon:9606]\nsynonym: \"lobus glandulae mammariae\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [BTO:0004718]\nxref: BTO:0004718\nxref: NCIT:C93232\nxref: UMLS:C0222616\nis_a: UBERON:0009912 ! anatomical lobe\nrelationship: has_part UBERON:0001912 ! lobule of mammary gland\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000310 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\"} ! breast\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001911 ! mammary gland\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002100 ! trunk\nproperty_value: editor_note \"The FMA class 'lactiferous gland' may be equivalent to this\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018231\nname: labyrinthine artery\ndef: \"A long slender branch of the anterior inferior cerebellar artery (85%-100% cases) or basilar artery (<15% cases), arises from near the middle of the artery; it accompanies the vestibulocochlear nerve through the internal acoustic meatus, and is distributed to the internal ear.\" [Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria auditiva interna\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria labyrinthi\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery]\nsynonym: \"artery of inner ear\" BROAD [FMA:50548]\nsynonym: \"internal auditory artery\" EXACT [FMA:50548]\nxref: EMAPA:37093 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:50548\nxref: NCIT:C32834\nxref: SCTID:148672009\nxref: Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:0009689 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\", cases=\"85-100%\", source=\"WP\"} ! anterior inferior cerebellar artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001633 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\", cases=\"15%\", source=\"WP\"} ! basilar artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001846 ! internal ear\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018240\nname: panniculus carnosus muscle\ndef: \"The skeletal muscle layer in the superficial fascia deep to the panniculus adiposus.\" [ISBN:0123813611, MP:0011157, Wikipedia:Panniculus_carnosus]\nsynonym: \"panniculus\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"panniculus carnosus\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"panniculus carnosus group\" EXACT [MA:0003141]\nxref: EMAPA:18189\nxref: EMAPS:1818928\nxref: MA:0003141\nxref: Wikipedia:Panniculus_carnosus\nis_a: UBERON:0008876 ! hypodermis skeletal muscle layer\nrelationship: attaches_to UBERON:0000976 {gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9265\", gci_relation=\"part_of\", notes=\"in the opossum the panniculus carnosis attaches to the humerus\", source=\"DOI:10.2307/1373999\", source=\"FEED:rd\"} ! humerus\nrelationship: deep_to UBERON:0013488 ! panniculus adiposus\nrelationship: in_taxon NCBITaxon:40674 ! Mammalia\nrelationship: innervated_by UBERON:0001780 {source=\"FFED:cw\"} ! spinal nerve\nrelationship: never_in_taxon NCBITaxon:9606 {notes=\"vestigial or barely detectable\"} ! Homo sapiens\nrelationship: present_in_taxon NCBITaxon:9261 {notes=\"by contraction of various parts of the panniculus carnosus, the short-beaked echidna can change shape, the most characteristic shape change being achieved by rolling itself into a ball when threatened, so protecting its belly and presenting a defensive array of sharp spines\"} ! Tachyglossus aculeatus\nproperty_value: function_notes \"They act to raise hair, quills, feathers, etc. It is also used in 'twitch' reflexes to shake off insects, etc.[Palaeos]\" xsd:string\nproperty_value: has_relational_adjective \"pannicular\" xsd:string\nproperty_value: structure_notes \"fine, flat muscles within the hypodermis. Their origin is in the deep fascia of bone and they insert into superficial skin.\" xsd:string\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"In humans, the platysma has features of the panniculaus carnosus[ISBN:0123813611].\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018535\nname: forelimb feather\ndef: \"A feather that is part of a forelimb.\" [http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"feather of forelimb\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000022 ! feather\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002102 ! forelimb\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000024 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:8782\"} ! forelimb wing\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0019221\nname: digit 1 or 5\ndef: \"Either of the outermost digits in a five-digit autopod, or their phylogenetic equivalent.\" [UBERON:cjm]\nsynonym: \"lateral digit\" RELATED HUMAN_PREFERRED []\nsynonym: \"outer digit\" RELATED HUMAN_PREFERRED []\nsynonym: \"outermost digit\" RELATED HUMAN_PREFERRED []\nis_a: UBERON:0002544 ! digit\nunion_of: UBERON:0006048 ! digit 1\nunion_of: UBERON:0006052 ! digit 5\nrelationship: in_lateral_side_of UBERON:0002470 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\"} ! autopod region\nproperty_value: seeAlso \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/592\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0022282\nname: secretion of Harderian gland\ndef: \"A merocrine secretion that is produced by a Harderian gland, containing lipids.\" [DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-76685-5_2]\nsynonym: \"Harderian gland fluid\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"Harderian gland secretion\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000456 ! secretion of exocrine gland\nintersection_of: composed_primarily_of CHEBI:18059 ! lipid\nintersection_of: produced_by UBERON:0015153 ! medial gland of ocular region\nrelationship: has_part CHEBI:8337 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9989\", source=\"PMID:7559104\"} ! porphyrin\nrelationship: produced_by UBERON:0004187 ! Harderian gland\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"in amphibians, chiefly seromucoid with some lipids[PMID:7559104]\" xsd:string\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"in birds, mucoid and lipid[PMID:7559104]\" xsd:string\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"in mammals, predominantly lipid; mucoid secretion restricted to extraglandular duct tissue[PMID:7559104]\" xsd:string\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"in the armadillo and opossum, mucous or serous acini may be present[PMID:7559104]\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0034900\nname: palatine process of premaxilla\ndef: \"Lingual ledge on the inner surface of the premaxilla.\" [AAO:0000414, AAO:LAP]\nsynonym: \"pars palatina of premaxilla\" EXACT [AAO:0000414]\nxref: AAO:0000414\nis_a: UBERON:0004529 ! anatomical projection\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002244 ! premaxilla\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0012074 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:40674\"} ! bony part of hard palate\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"A posterior extension of the premaxilla that lies along the palatine and fuses to some extent with it. In the Passeres it may be fused, unfused, free or a lateral flange. Evolved multiple times in Passerines [http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/part/29066]\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0034919\nname: juvenile stage\ndef: \"The stage of being no more dependent of the nest and/or from caregivers for subsistence while having not reach sexual maturity.\" [Bgee:AN, https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/645]\nis_a: UBERON:0000105 ! life cycle stage\nrelationship: immediately_preceded_by UBERON:0034920 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:40674\"} ! infant stage\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000112 ! sexually immature stage\nrelationship: preceded_by UBERON:0007221 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:32524\"} ! neonate stage\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:2001053\nname: future internal carotid artery\nsynonym: \"PICA\" EXACT [TAO:0001053]\nsynonym: \"primitive internal carotid artery\" EXACT [ZFA:0001053]\nxref: EFO:0003612\nxref: TAO:0001053\nxref: ZFA:0001053\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0003120 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:40674\", source=\"EHDAA2\"} ! pharyngeal arch artery 3\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0004363 ! pharyngeal arch artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001530 {source=\"EHDAA2\"} ! common carotid artery plus branches\n\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\nONSISTENT [FMA:7183]\nsynonym: \"upper limb and pectoral girdle\" RELATED HUMAN_PREFERRED [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"upper limb and shoulder\" RELATED [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nxref: EMAPA:37860 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:7183\nxref: SCTID:110716002\nxref: VSAO:0000213\nintersection_of: UBERON:0010707 ! appendage girdle complex\nintersection_of: has_part UBERON:0001421 ! pectoral girdle region\nrelationship: has_skeleton UBERON:0012475 ! skeleton of pectoral complex\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000153 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:32523\"} ! anterior region of body\nproperty_value: external_definition \"Appendage girdle complex that when present, encompasses the pectoral appendage and half of the pectoral girdle.[VSAO]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-08-14\", external_class=\"VSAO:0000213\", ontology=\"VSAO\", source=\"VSAO:MAH\"}\nproperty_value: external_ontology_notes \"note that the FMA uses the terms 'upper limb' and 'lower limb' to refer to the entire appendage complex (free limb plus girdle region)\" xsd:string {external_ontology=\"FMA\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0010709\nname: pelvic complex\ndef: \"Appendage girdle complex that when present, encompasses the pelvic appendicular skeleton and the pelvic girdle.\" [VSAO:0000215]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsynonym: \"lower limb\" RELATED INCONSISTENT [FMA:7184]\nsynonym: \"lower limb and pelvic girdle\" RELATED HUMAN_PREFERRED [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"lower limb and pelvis\" RELATED [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"pelvic appendage/girdle complex\" EXACT [VSAO:0000215]\nsynonym: \"pelvic girdle plus pelvic limb or fin\" EXACT [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"pelvic girdle plus posterior limb or fin\" EXACT [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nxref: EMAPA:37863 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:7184\nxref: SCTID:416631005\nxref: VSAO:0000215\nintersection_of: UBERON:0010707 ! appendage girdle complex\nintersection_of: has_part UBERON:0001271 ! pelvic girdle region\nrelationship: has_skeleton UBERON:0012476 ! skeleton of pelvic complex\nrelationship: mutually_spatially_disjoint_with UBERON:0010708 ! pectoral complex\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000154 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:32523\"} ! posterior region of body\nproperty_value: external_definition \"Appendage girdle complex that when present, encompasses the pelvic appendage and the pelvic girdle.[VSAO]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-08-14\", external_class=\"VSAO:0000215\", ontology=\"VSAO\", source=\"VSAO:MAH\"}\nproperty_value: external_ontology_notes \"note that the FMA uses the terms 'upper limb' and 'lower limb' to refer to the entire appendage complex (free limb plus girdle region). Note the MA class 'hindlimb' may also belong here\" xsd:string {external_ontology=\"FMA\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0010757\nname: rib 8\ndef: \"The eighth rib counting from the top of the rib cage down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].\" [http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165, ncithesaurus:Rib_8]\nsubset: defined_by_ordinal_series\nsynonym: \"costa VIII\" EXACT OMO:0003011 []\nsynonym: \"eighth rib\" EXACT [FMA:8120]\nsynonym: \"upper false rib\" NARROW [NCBITaxon:9606, PMCID:PMC1327870]\nxref: EMAPA:19536\nxref: FMA:8120\nxref: MA:0001408\nxref: NCIT:C52760\nxref: SCTID:244663007\nxref: UMLS:C1709954 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Rib_8\"}\nis_a: UBERON:0002228 ! rib\nis_a: UBERON:0002238 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\", source=\"FMA\"} ! false rib\nproperty_value: curator_notes \"elements are to be defined spatially/topologically\" xsd:string\nproperty_value: rib_number \"8\" xsd:nonNegativeInteger\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"Typically a false rib in humans but may sometimes be a true one due to sternal attachment\" xsd:string {source=\"PMC1327870\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0010940\nname: muscle of digastric group\ndef: \"Either of the two muscles that comprise the digastric group (anterior or posterior).\" [http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"belly of digastric\" NARROW [FMA:46297]\nsynonym: \"belly of digastric muscle\" RELATED [FMA:46297]\nsynonym: \"digastric\" RELATED [FMA:46291]\nsynonym: \"digastric belly\" NARROW [FMA:46297]\nsynonym: \"digastric muscle\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Digastric_muscle]\nsynonym: \"digastricus\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Digastric_muscle]\nsynonym: \"muscle body proper of digastric\" RELATED [FMA:46297]\nsynonym: \"musculus digastricus\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Digastric_muscle]\nxref: FMA:46297\nxref: SCTID:360772008\nis_a: UBERON:0010938 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\", source=\"FMA\"} ! muscle belly\nintersection_of: UBERON:0014892 ! skeletal muscle organ, vertebrate\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0001562 ! digastric muscle group\nproperty_value: external_ontology_notes \"FMA represents this as a muscle belly, but this classification does not work well across mammals (pers. comm., FEED:rd), so we classify this is a distinct muscle organ here.\" xsd:string {external_ontology=\"FMA\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0010944\nname: posterior digastric muscle\ndef: \"The posterior digastric is a pharyngeal arch II muscle that participates in oral pharyngeal behavior, is innervated by the digastric branch of facial nerve and attaches to the posterior cranial base and the hyoid apparatus. It is found superficial to the mylohyoid muscle.\" [MFMO:0000060]\nsynonym: \"digastric, posterior\" EXACT [FEED:FEED]\nsynonym: \"digastricus posterior\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"digastricus posterior belly\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"digastricus, venter caudalis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"m. digastricus posterior\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"posterior belly of digastric\" EXACT [FMA:46303]\nsynonym: \"posterior belly of digastric muscle\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"posterior digastric\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"posterior digastric muscle\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"venter posterior musculus digastrici\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [FMA:46303, FMA:TA]\nxref: EMAPA:37406 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:46303\nxref: MFMO:0000060\nxref: SCTID:141905002\nis_a: UBERON:0010940 ! muscle of digastric group\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0003066 ! pharyngeal arch 2\nrelationship: has_muscle_insertion UBERON:0006959 {gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9599\", gci_relation=\"part_of\", source=\"DOI:10.1007/BF02547558\"} ! mandible angular process\nrelationship: has_muscle_origin UBERON:0001678 ! temporal bone\nrelationship: has_muscle_origin UBERON:0011220 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\", source=\"Wikipedia:Digastric_muscle\", source=\"Wikipedia:Mastoid_process\"} ! mastoid process of temporal bone\nrelationship: innervated_by UBERON:0011315 {notes=\"digastric branch\", source=\"FEED\", source=\"Wikipedia\"} ! digastric branch of facial nerve\nproperty_value: external_definition \"The posterior digastric is a pharyngeal arch II muscle that participates in oral pharyngeal behavior, is innervated by the digastric branchi of facial nerve and attaches to the posterior cranial base.[FEED]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-07-02\", ontology=\"FEED\", url=\"http://www.feedexp.org\"}\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"in orangutans, this muscle attaches to the mandible rather than the hyoid\" xsd:string {source=\"DOI:10.1007/BF02547558\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0011265\nname: carpometacarpal joint of digit 1\ndef: \"A carpometacarpal joint that connects to metacarpal 1.\" [Wikipedia:Carpometacarpal_joint#Thumb]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsynonym: \"carpometacarpal joint of digit I\" EXACT COMPARATIVE_PREFERRED [https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/458]\nsynonym: \"carpometacarpal joint of pollex\" EXACT [FMA:35421]\nsynonym: \"carpometacarpal joint of the thumb\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Carpometacarpal_joint#Thumb]\nsynonym: \"carpometacarpal joint of thumb\" EXACT [FMA:35421]\nsynonym: \"TMJ\" RELATED INCONSISTENT [Wikipedia:Carpometacarpal_joint#Thumb]\nsynonym: \"trapeziometacarpal joint\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Carpometacarpal_joint#Thumb]\nxref: FMA:35421\nxref: SCTID:361843007\nxref: Wikipedia:Carpometacarpal_joint#Thumb\nis_a: UBERON:0011965 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\", source=\"Wikipedia\"} ! saddle joint\nintersection_of: UBERON:0011119 ! carpometacarpal joint\nintersection_of: connects UBERON:0003645 ! metacarpal bone of digit 1\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"In humans it connects the trapezium to the first metacarpal bone, plays an irreplaceable role in the normal functioning of the thumb. The most important joint connecting the wrist to the metacarpus, osteoarthritis of the TMC is a severely disabling condition; up to twenty times more common among old women than in average\" xsd:string {source=\"WP\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0011510\nname: cloacal bursa\ndef: \"An evagination of the cloaca. In Testudines these are hypothesized to function in different physiological roles, primarily in respiration.\" [PMID:11479904, UBERON:cjm]\ncomment: Taxon notes: in cryptodires, bursae apparently function primarily in buoyancy control and secondarily in ion transport and nesting, but several pleurodires have been shown recently to use them in aquatic respiration.[PMID:11479904]\nis_a: UBERON:0000063 ! organ subunit\nrelationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0007585 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:8459\", notes=\"cloacal bursa\"} ! respiratory gaseous exchange by respiratory system\nrelationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0031413 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:8464\", source=\"PMID:11479904\"} ! regulation of buoyancy\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000162 ! cloaca\nproperty_value: depiction \"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d8/Turtle_Cloacal_Respiration.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0011576\nname: supraorbital ridge\ndef: \"The superior half of the orbital rim, which constitutes the curved superior border of the orbital opening, formed by the frontal bone.\" [http://www.medilexicon.com/medicaldictionary.php?t=52809]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsynonym: \"arcus superciliaris\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge]\nsynonym: \"eyebrow bone\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge]\nsynonym: \"frontal torus\" NARROW SENSU [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge]\nsynonym: \"frontal torus\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge]\nsynonym: \"margin of the orbit\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge]\nsynonym: \"margo supraorbitalis\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [FMA:53097, FMA:TA]\nsynonym: \"margo supraorbitalis (os frontale)\" RELATED [FMA:53097]\nsynonym: \"orbital ridge\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"superciliary ridge\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge]\nsynonym: \"superior orbital rim\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"supra-orbital border of frontal bone\" RELATED [FMA:53097]\nsynonym: \"supra-orbital margin\" EXACT [FMA:317104]\nsynonym: \"supra-orbital margin of frontal bone\" RELATED [FMA:53097]\nsynonym: \"supra-orbital ridge\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"supraorbital arch\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge]\nsynonym: \"supraorbital margin\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"supraorbital margin\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge]\nsynonym: \"supraorbital margin of frontal bone\" RELATED [FMA:53097]\nsynonym: \"supraorbital surface of frontal bone\" RELATED [FMA:57137]\nsynonym: \"supraorbital torus\" NARROW SENSU [NCBITaxon:63221, Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge]\nsynonym: \"supraorbital torus\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge]\nxref: FMA:317104\nxref: NCIT:C82953\nxref: SCTID:280550003\nxref: UMLS:C2826587 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Orbital_Ridge\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Supraorbital_ridge\nis_a: UBERON:0005913 ! zone of bone organ\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:2000691 ! supraorbital bone\nrelationship: has_quality PATO:0001598 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:63221\"} ! protruding\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000209 ! tetrapod frontal bone\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0035849 ! orbital margin\nrelationship: present_in_taxon NCBITaxon:63221 ! Homo sapiens neanderthalensis\nrelationship: seeAlso FMA:53097\nrelationship: seeAlso FMA:57137\nproperty_value: external_ontology_notes \"see also: 'supraorbital flange'. FMA has 2 related classes, but these refer to the line and surface\" xsd:string {external_ontology=\"FMA\"}\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"Neanderthals have a Supraorbital torus, a prominent, trabecular (spongy) brow ridge.\" xsd:string {source=\"Wikipedia:Neanderthal_anatomy\", taxon=\"NCBITaxon:63221\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0011583\nname: stylopodial skeleton\ndef: \"Proximal element of a free limb skeleton consisting of the femur and humerus in the forelimb stylopodium and hindlimb stylopodium respectively[VSAO, modified].\" [VSAO:0005007]\nsynonym: \"mesomere 1\" RELATED HOMOLOGY [ISBN:0226313409]\nsynonym: \"propodial skeleton\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"propodium\" RELATED [VSAO:0005007]\nsynonym: \"proximal metapterygial mesomere\" RELATED HOMOLOGY [ISBN:0226313409]\nsynonym: \"stylopod\" RELATED [VSAO:0005007]\nsynonym: \"stylopodium\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"stylopodium skeleton\" EXACT []\nxref: VSAO:0005007\nintersection_of: UBERON:0010912 ! subdivision of skeleton\nintersection_of: skeleton_of UBERON:0002472 ! stylopod\nrelationship: distally_connected_to UBERON:0011584 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:32523\"} ! zeugopodial skeleton\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002472 ! stylopod\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0004381 {source=\"VSAO\"} ! skeleton of limb\nproperty_value: external_definition \"Proximal element of the limb skeleton consisting of the femur and humerus in the forelimb stylopodium and hindlimb stylopodium respectively.[VSAO]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-08-14\", external_class=\"VSAO:0005007\", ontology=\"VSAO\", source=\"VSAO:NI\"}\nproperty_value: has_relational_adjective \"propodial\" xsd:string\nproperty_value: has_relational_adjective \"stylopodial\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0011584\nname: zeugopodial skeleton\ndef: \"Section of the forelimb skeleton located between the stylopodium and the autopodium.\" [VSAO:0005010]\nsynonym: \"epipodial skeleton\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"epipodium\" RELATED [VSAO:0005010]\nsynonym: \"m