{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778977921649,"sessionID":"ses_1ccaa862effe2snTZoyFM1CJi8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_x34Fgbmi0n8PsBrReCY1vBeq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- restricted `neurula stage` and `pharyngula stage` to `Chordata`\n+- changed the `late embryonic stage -> preceded_by pharyngula stage` axiom to a chordate-qualified GCI so the broad late embryo classes are no longer globally tied to chordate-specific stages\n+\n+This keeps `late embryo` / `late embryonic stage` broadly applicable while preserving the vertebrate/chordate developmental ordering where appropriate.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+This change addresses issue `#3478` by removing an overly broad link from general late embryonic classes to effectively chordate-specific developmental stages.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+- updated `UBERON:0000110` (`neurula stage`) from `in_taxon NCBITaxon:6072 ! Eumetazoa` to `in_taxon NCBITaxon:7711 ! Chordata`\n+- updated `UBERON:0004707` (`pharyngula stage`) from `in_taxon NCBITaxon:6072 ! Eumetazoa` to `in_taxon NCBITaxon:7711 ! Chordata`\n+- changed `UBERON:0007220` (`late embryonic stage`) so `preceded_by UBERON:0004707 ! pharyngula stage` is no longer global, and instead applies only with the taxon-qualified GCI `{gci_relation=\"in_taxon\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:7711\"}`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- the issue report correctly identified that `pharyngula` and `neurula` are chordate-specific concepts in practice\n+- `late embryo` and `late embryonic stage` should remain broadly applicable across metazoans, so they should not globally inherit a temporal dependency on `pharyngula stage`\n+- the taxon-qualified GCI preserves the developmental ordering for chordates without leaking that constraint into the general class\n+\n+Valida